cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.NE. 

The paper deals with information theory and machine learning, which are covered by several arXiv CS sub-categories. cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on measures of shared, unique, and complementary information. cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely categories as the paper discusses decision theory and multivariate information decomposition, which are relevant to these fields. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are less likely categories, but still possible as the paper touches on the interpretation of information in the multivariate setting, which could be relevant to these fields.
